text: And actually, the interview felt a lot looser and more natural after that; a tough thing when you're speaking through a translator. So I guess the moral of the story is, embrace chaos?

I have to grab my dog and hold her up to the screen to prove that it is not, in fact, a ghost, but my stupid dog. 

FWIW, despite my humiliation, Mikami was a great sport. He actually ran up to the camera to get a closer look at her.

I kind of just ignore it and power through. Mikami notices, though, but he can only see a shaking plant behind me. Next thing I know, he's pointing at me and yelling. His translator tells me he thinks it's a ghost.

About halfway through the interview, though, she got real antsy. I have a fake plant in a wicker basket, so she, wanting attention and being a brat, starts yanking on the basket. The plant, but not the basket and my dog, is visible in the bottom corner of my screen.

It also took place at 7pm for me because of the time difference. My dog, who I had only gotten a couple of weeks prior, did not like this. Evenings are cuddle time. Despite this, she was okay for the first hour or so.

In honor of Ghostwire Tokyo's release, I'll share one of the most embarrassing interview moments I've ever had. I had a long interview with Shinji Mikami for this story. It lasted about two hours, in part because we were speaking through a translator. https://t.co/erBKee1iCG

Did The Suicide Squad flop in its debut? That's a very complicated question, and honestly, probably not one that any of us can answer right now, especially when you can't quantify the value it's added to HBO Max! I wrote more about that here: https://t.co/sp05YdWyfT

@ChrisContinues Right — I don’t even see why it’s being compared to F9 or Black Widow, since neither of those movies were offered to streaming subscribers for free. That’s easily the biggest factor here.

OBVIOUSLY that’s going to negatively impact the box office. I think that contributed to TSS’s low numbers much more than the R-rating or even the Delta variant. But for WB, making HBO Max THAT valuable might be worth it in the long run.

In the past year, HBO Max has proven to be one of the most important streaming services to have. Anecdotally, it’s the one I use the most by a long shot. The day-and-date releases are a big part of that.

I don’t envy box office reporters this weekend, because The Suicide Squad “bombing” is… complicated. But I disagree with some of the sentiment I’m seeing that releasing it day-and-date on HBO Max was a mistake.
